# .env.example — the NAMES of secret values this project expects.
#
# This file is committed and lists variable NAMES ONLY, always with empty values.
# Real values live ONLY in your local environment (or a git-ignored .env /
# application-local.yml) and are NEVER committed — Git history is forever.
#
# No secrets are needed yet. Entries appear here the moment a lesson
# introduces one (database password, JWT secret, AI provider key, ...).
